<dl id="n03024a"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n03" href="#n03024a">N03 (VI.B.3)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n03all.htm#n03024a"> 24(a)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> mendicant orders / (SD) / introduced 900 &frasl; 1000</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources"> <mark>Mendicant orders</mark> whose members were dependent chiefly on the offerings of the faithful for subsistence did not exist in Ireland at this time, and were not introduced until <mark>many centuries later</mark>. <small> J.M. Flood, <a name="JMFI" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#JMFI"><cite title="source">Ireland: Its Saints and Scholars</cite></a> (n.d) 59</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
